Package: FinancialFunctions
Title: Excel-Compatible Financial Functions Powered by Rust
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Tor", "Storli", email = "your.email@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides 55 Excel-compatible financial functions implemented in
    Rust for high performance. Functions cover annuity calculations (FV, PV,
    PMT, IPMT, PPMT, CUMIPMT, CUMPRINC, NPER, RATE, ISPMT), cash flow
    analysis (NPV, IRR, MIRR, XNPV, XIRR), depreciation (SLN, SYD, DB, DDB,
    VDB, AMORLINC, AMORDEGRC), coupon date calculations (COUPDAYBS, COUPDAYS,
    COUPDAYSNC, COUPNCD, COUPPCD, COUPNUM), bond and security pricing (PRICE,
    PRICEDISC, PRICEMAT, YIELD, YIELDDISC, YIELDMAT, DISC, INTRATE, RECEIVED,
    DURATION, MDURATION, ACCRINT, ACCRINTM), and miscellaneous functions
    (EFFECT, NOMINAL, DOLLARDE, DOLLARFR, FVSCHEDULE, RRI, PDURATION,
    TBILLPRICE, TBILLYIELD, TBILLEQ, ODDFPRICE, ODDFYIELD, ODDLPRICE,
    ODDLYIELD). All functions match Excel output and handle invalid inputs
    gracefully by returning NA.
